{{IMP/exo|
Show that a rocket of mass <math>m</math> that ejects at speed <math>u</math> (with respect to
itself) a part of its mass <math>dm</math> by time unit <math>dt</math> moves in the sense opposed
to <math>u</math>. Give the movement law for a rocket with speed zero at time <math>t=0</math>,
located in a earth gravitational field considered as constant. 
}}

{{IMP/exo|
''Doppler effect.''  Consider a light source <math>S</math> moving at constant speed
with respect to reference frame <math>R</math>. Using wave four-vector <math>(k,\omega/c)</math> give
the relation between frequencies measured by an experimentator moving with <math>S</math>
and another experimentater attached to <math>R</math>. What about sound waves?
}}

{{IMP/exo|
For a cylindrical coordinates system, metrics <math>g_{ij}</math> of the space is:
{{IMP/eq|<math>
ds^2=dr^2+r^2d\theta^2+dz^2
</math>}}
Calculate the Christoffel symbols <math>\Gamma^{i}_{hk}</math> defined by:
{{IMP/eq|<math>
\Gamma^{i}_{hk}=\frac{1}{2}g^{ij} (\partial_hg_{kj}+ \partial_kg_{hj}-
\partial_jg_{hk})
</math>}}
}}
{{IMP/exo|
Consider a unit mass in a three dimensional reference frame whose metrics is:
{{IMP/eq|<math>
ds^2=g_{ij}dq_idq_j
</math>}}
Show that the kinetic energy of the system is:
{{IMP/eq|<math>
E_c=\frac{1}{2}g_{ij}\dot q_i\dot q_j
</math>}}
Show that the fundamental equation of dynamics is written here (forces are
assumed to derive from a potential <math>V</math>) :
{{IMP/eq|<math>
\frac{D\dot q_i}{Dt}=-\frac{\partial V}{\partial q_i}
</math>}}
}}

